other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 9 mm with associated minimal wall thickening and surrounding inflammatory changes/fat stranding in the right lower quadrant; findings are compatible with acute uncomplicated appendicitis. There is an 8 mm hypodensity in segment VIII of the liver likely representing a cyst. Mild atherosclerosis of the abdominal aorta without aneurysmal dilatation, dissection, or flow-limiting stenosis.
